about.summary: A Davidian curve defines a seminonparametric density, whose shape and flexibility can be tuned by easy to estimate parameters. Since a special case of a Davidian curve is the standard normal density, Davidian curves can be used for relaxing normality assumption in statistical applications (Zhang & Davidian, 2001) <doi:10.1111/j.0006-341X.2001.00795.x>. This package provides the density function, the gradient of the loglikelihood and a random generator for Davidian curves.

name: r-dcurver
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.9.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-dcurver
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: dcurver_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/dcurver_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/dcurver/dcurver_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d65d7f33d4961bcce7e2ac2568aed0ae13ef582a71b497bf5674c49a8704deb1

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1003
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}          # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}    # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}  # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - llvm-openmp                  # [osx]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.14
    - r-rcpparmadillo
  run:
    - r-base
    - llvm-openmp                # [osx]
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.14
    - r-rcpparmadillo

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('dcurver')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('dcurver')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/oguzhanogreden/dcurver
  license: GPL-3
  summary: A Davidian curve defines a seminonparametric density, whose shape and flexibility
    can be tuned by easy to estimate parameters. Since a special case of a Davidian
    curve is the standard normal density, Davidian curves can be used for relaxing normality
    assumption in statistical applications (Zhang & Davidian, 2001) <doi:10.1111/j.0006-341X.2001.00795.x>.
    This package provides the density function, the gradient of the loglikelihood and
    a random generator for Davidian curves.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.0
